    "what_description": "Dryopetalon palmeri is a species of flowering plant that belongs to the family Brassicaceae. It is a perennial herb that grows up to 1 meter in height, with a branching stem and alternate, linear to lanceolate leaves that are 5-20 cm long. The plant produces white or cream-colored flowers in a raceme or panicle, with 4 petals and 6 stamens, and it fruits in a siliqua (a type of dehiscent fruit) that is 5-15 cm long and 1-2 cm wide. The plant is native to Mexico and the southwestern United States, and it typically grows in dry, sandy areas with full sun. The species was first described by Palmer in 1888.",
